OL,4,Cpotholes
OL,6,FRoads Minister, Guy Opperman said,
OL,7,F"Motorists and roads users in Kent
OL,8,Fdeserve safe, modern and smooth roads
OL,9,Fthey can rely on. That's why it's
OL,10,Fgreat to see Kent County Council
OL,11,Fmaking the most of the additional
OL,12,Ffunding from the Government to tackle
OL,13,Froad defects and speed-up journeys."
OL,15,F"As we continue to put drivers back in
OL,16,Fthe driving seat, the #135 million of
OL,17,Fadditional funding we are providing
OL,18,Fover the next 11 years will help
OL,19,Fensure that more and more roads all
OL,20,Facross Kent can be resurfaced."
